---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Jason Enia - Speaking & Media"
  description="Selected keynote addresses, panel presentations, and public commentary."
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 md:py-24 px-4">
    <header class="mb-12 md:mb-16">
      <h1
        class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight text-charcoal dark:text-softcream mb-3"
      >
        Speaking & Media
      </h1>
      <p
        class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-normal max-w-2xl leading-tight"
      >
        Selected talks, presentations, and public commentary.
      </p>
      <div class="w-16 h-px bg-rust-500/60 mt-8"></div>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-16">
      <!-- Invited Talks Section -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-4">
          <h2
            class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-4 md:sticky md:top-32"
          >
            Invited Talks
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-8 space-y-16">
          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >Houston World Affairs Council &bull; Houston, TX &bull; 2024</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors mb-4"
            >
              The Madness of Nukes
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
            >
              Delivered to the World Affairs Council Summer Program, this talk
              explored how nuclear intensify security dilemmas and create the
              counterintuitive logic of deterrence that creates paradoxes for
              modern peace.
            </p>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://wachouston.org/global-scholars-academy/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors ml-auto"
              >
                Learn About The Program <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >Central Police University &bull; Taoyuan, Taiwan &bull; 2017</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors mb-4"
            >
              The Politics of Disasters: Three Observations from 2017
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
            >
              Challenging the conventional 'When will we learn?' narrative, this
              talk explores why political incentives often override
              institutional learning after a catastrophe. By analyzing flood
              insurance, disaster relief, and price gouging laws, I demonstrate
              how bad policies often make for very good politics.
            </p>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="/documents/Enia_Politics_of_Disasters_2017.pdf"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors ml-auto"
              >
                View Slides <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >PRAGUE NUCLEAR SCHOLARS PROGRAM &bull; PRAGUE, CZECH REPUBLIC
                &bull; 2018 &bull; WITH JEFFREY FIELDS</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors mb-4"
            >
              On the Health of the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Regime
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
            >
              Arguing that we should stop confusing the health of the NPT with
              the health of the entire regime, we introduced a multidimensional
              framework that moves the analysis of the regime beyond the
              pervasive 'crisis' narrative and better illuminates the way the
              regime's institutions and norms structure global cooperation.
            </p>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://youtu.be/LIPU-gBs8sc?si=AujbTZ-jYPGcrxzJ&t=3859"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors ml-auto"
              >
                Watch The Panel <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-t border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10" />

      <!-- Panel Presentations Section -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-4">
          <h2
            class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-4 md:sticky md:top-32"
          >
            Panel Presentations
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-8 space-y-16">
          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >FLACSO-ISA JOINT CONFERENCE &bull; QUITO, ECUADOR &bull; 2018</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors mb-4"
            >
              A Political Economy Approach to the Form and Function of the
              Nuclear Suppliers Group
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
            >
              The conceptual foundation for my 2020 JPND article. Using a
              transaction cost framework, this presentation demonstrated how the
              Nuclear Suppliers Group acts as the essential 'grease' for
              international cooperation, solving coordination hurdles the NPT
              cannot address alone.
            </p>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://www.isanet.org/Conferences/FLACSO-Quito-2018/Program"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors ml-auto"
              >
                VIEW CONFERENCE PROGRAM <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >NATURAL HAZARDS CENTER &bull; BOULDER, CO &bull; 2016</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors mb-4"
            >
              The Emerging Global Disaster Risk Management System
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
            >
              The precursor to my 2020 research in Progress in Disaster Science.
              This talk explored the evolution of global risk frameworks,
              arguing that the shift toward a more integrated, systemic approach
              to disaster management represents a fundamental change in
              international coordination.
            </p>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://hazards.colorado.edu/workshop/2016/session/the-emerging-global-disaster-risk-management-system"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors ml-auto"
              >
                VIEW WORKSHOP PROGRAM <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-t border-charcoal/10 dark:border-softcream/10" />

      <!-- Public Commentary Section -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-4">
          <h2
            class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-4 md:sticky md:top-32"
          >
            Public Commentary
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-8 space-y-16">
          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >Foundation for Economic Education &bull; 2017</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors mb-4"
            >
              Why There Are No Mops to Clean Up Texas
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
            >
              An analysis of the unintended consequences of anti-price gouging
              laws following Hurricane Harvey. By breaking the price mechanism,
              these institutional rules worsened local shortages of critical
              supplies and left vulnerable populations at greater risk.
            </p>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://fee.org/articles/why-there-are-no-mops-to-clean-up-texas/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors"
              >
                Read Op-Ed <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >The Courier of Montgomery County &bull; 2020 &bull; With Y.
                Yang</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors mb-4"
            >
              Effective Information Can Help Fight COVID-19 Anxiety
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-sans font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
            >
              Contrary to the myth of mass panic, humans facing a crisis
              actively seek out information to navigate uncertainty. This piece
              examines the vital role local institutions play in delivering that
              information and stabilizing public behavior.
            </p>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://www.yourconroenews.com/neighborhood/moco/opinion/article/SHSU-leaders-Effective-information-can-help-15171539.php"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors"
              >
                Read Op-Ed <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
